	<p>
	I'm Zephyr Cady — an engineer and AI practitioner with 13 years of experience across cybersecurity, 
project management, and high-assurance systems. I currently lead a data science and AI team at the 
Naval Nuclear Laboratory, where I oversee applied ML and AI initiatives supporting the U.S. Navy's 
nuclear propulsion program.

This site is where I think out loud about AI safety — technical alignment research, 
eval methodology, and what rigorous engineering culture from high-consequence domains 
has to offer the field. I'm particularly interested in the intersection of control, 
interpretability, and deployment safety in regulated environments.

If you're working on evals, red-teaming, or alignment research and want to talk, reach me at 
zephyrcady@gmail[.]com.
